description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term post to 31st March 2022 due to funding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Hywel Dda Health Board employee this post will only be offered on a secondment basis and you will need to have gained your line managers approval for the secondment prior to going to interview.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and motivated individual to fill the role of ICT Project Manager.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post-holder will be responsible for managing and controlling the delivery of ICT projects which form part of the Clinical Systems Programme and is key to the successful implementation of the Health Board&#39;s Strategy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will work closely with our ICT, Programme &amp; Systems and Information teams to support implementation of the ICT programme objectives, which will contribute to an organisational innovation that delivers high quality patient care. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants should be educated to Degree level and possess management qualification or equivalent experience. They will also have extensive experience of working in a project management role and experience of achieving ambitious targets and implementing ICT solutions. Applicants should possess PRINCE2 Practitioner or equivalent professional project management qualification. Applications should have excellent communication, negotiation, persuasion and influencing skills and be a strong project manager.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Any exposure to ITIL based Service Management transition would also be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 26th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
